# Lock golden-fixture line endings to LF — UPDATE_GOLDEN=1 regenerates
# them under whatever local autocrlf setting the dev has, and CI does
# byte-equal comparison. Without this attribute, a Windows dev's git add
# would silently CRLF-convert the fixtures, breaking CI.
internal/observability/replay/testdata/golden/*.json text eol=lf

# Lock recompute-shadow capture fixtures to LF for the same reason. The
# TestDataCleanerRecompute_ShadowMode_TickerBasket capture regenerates these
# on every run; the byte-identity gate (git diff --quiet) is meaningful only
# when line endings are stable across Windows/Unix dev machines. (DC-1 Phase 4
# regenerated these intentionally — the §8.2.1 Option A umbrella-dual-write
# deletion makes the post-clean TotalAssets umbrella diverge further from its
# components, which the shadow shim faithfully records.)
internal/integration/testdata/recompute-shadow/*.json text eol=lf
